Import Scanner

Main

    Declare Integer factorial = 1
    Declare Integer input = 0

    Scanner scan = new Scanner

    Display "Enter a number between 1 and 10 (Enter 0 to exit): "
    input = scan

    While (input != 0)  

        If input &gt;= 1 AND input &lt;= 10

                For Integer ii = factorial to input Step -1

                    factorial = factorial * ii

                End For

            Display factorial

            factorial = 1

            Display "Enter a number between 1 and 10 (Enter 0 to exit): "   
            input = scan  

        Else

            Display "The number you entered was not between 1 and 10."
            Display "Re-enter a number between 1 and 10(Enter 0 to exit): "
            input = scan

        End If

    End While

    Close Scanner

    Display "Goodbye!"

End Main
</code></pre> Java - Factorial (Loops)<pre><code>// Factorial (Loops) - Java- In Person Session
// Date: 2024-06-06
// Author: Steve Ellermann
// Note: Corrected version

import java.util.Scanner;

public class FactorialUsingLoops {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Scanner scan = new Scanner(System.in);

        int factorial = 1;
        int input = 0;

        System.out.print("Enter a number between 1 and 10 (Enter 0 to exit): ");
        input = scan.nextInt();

        while (input != 0) {

            if (input &gt;= 1 &amp;&amp; input &lt;= 10) {

                for (int ii = factorial; ii &lt;= input; ii++) { // for loop - fixed - changed code
                    factorial *= ii;
                }

                System.out.println("\n" + input + "! = " + factorial);

                factorial = 1; // reset factorial to 1 - fixed - added code

                System.out.print("\nEnter a number between 1 and 10 (Enter 0 to exit): ");
                input = scan.nextInt();
            } else {
                System.out.print("\nThe number you entered was not between 1 and 10.");
                System.out.print("\nRe-enter a number between 1 and 10 (Enter 0 to exit): ");
                input = scan.nextInt();
            }
        }
        scan.close(); // close the scanner object - fixed - added code
        System.out.println("\nGoodbye!");
    }

}
</code></pre> <p>Let's see what happens when we run corrected the code. Try the corrected FactorialUsingLoops.java Java program in the Online Playground IDE</p> <p>Note</p> <ul> <li>Try the corrected FactorialUsingLoops.java Java program in the Online Playground IDE</li> </ul>

